<section>
	<h2>Purpose</h2>
	<p>Emulates MathML support for browsers that do not have native MathML support.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Use when</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Adding scientific or mathematical formulas to a web page.</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Working example</h2>
	<p><a href="../../../demos/mathml/mathml-en.html">English example</a></p>
	<p><a href="../../../demos/mathml/mathml-fr.html">French example</a></p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>How to implement</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Code any formulas to include in a Web page in MathML and insert the MathML code into the HTML code using the <code>&lt;math&gt;</code> element. The polyfill is automatically loaded in browsers that do not have MathML support.</li>
	</ol>
	<p><b>Note: </b> The MathML polyfill depends on <a href="http://www.mathjax.org/">MathJax</a> which is loaded from the MathJaX CDN.</p>
</section>

